                <note rend="inline" type="source">662.11241/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 31, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. Your 293, December 31, 9 a.m.<note n="92" xml:id="d1096fn92">Not
                        printed.</note> German consular officers and clerks in United States enjoy
                    privilege of free importation on basis of reciprocity. You are granted
                    authorization to inform Foreign Office in this sense, as requested in your
                    despatch No. 5142, December 9, 1929.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
